http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Student-commits-suicide/article14015096.ece

A ninth standard student staying in a government hostel at Balagadi, near Koppa, allegedly committed suicide by hanging himself on Thursday. The Koppa police gave the name of the deceased as Chethan (15), son of Pushpa, a resident of Karadi Khan Estate, near Bidare in Chikkamagaluru taluk.The student had attempted suicide by hanging himself to the ceiling of the hostel room, which was noticed by his fellow students. Although he was immediately taken to a nearby hospital, he died there. It was said the boy was suffering from stomach pain. The Koppa police have registered a case.